    "description": "Contrary to the comments in #467, it turns out it's actually not terribly complicated to get this working. Basically, if we are passed in an excluded field, we add it to the new `override_fields` list. We use this list to keep track of the excluded fields that the user explicitly wants us to create plots for.\r\n\r\nTo get this working, I had to thread the `fields` list into the `PlotWindow` base class initializer. The other option was to functionally duplicate code in each of `SlicePlot`, `ProjectionPlot`, and `OffAxisSlicePlot`, so I went with an extra keyword in the base class as the lesser of two evils.\r\n\r\nOne wrinkle: it's still not possible to plot excluded fields when the plot is created via `to_pw`. I'm not going to try to get that working since it would require refactoring how field names are stored in data objects.\r\n\r\nSorry for creating this PR twice, I made a mistake in one of my commit messages that forced me to recreate the whole PR to get the correct commit message included.",
